From: Ivan Anishchuk <ivan@ivananishchuk.net>
Subject: [PATCH] fix AttributeError: portage.versions.cmp_sort_key

Recent Portage releases (>= ~3.0.77) removed cmp_sort_key from the
portage.versions module; the function still exists under portage.util
which is where the rest of Portage now imports it from. Update the
single call site in overlint so it stops crashing with:

  AttributeError: module 'portage.versions' has no attribute 'cmp_sort_key'.
  Did you mean: 'cpv_sort_key'?

cpv_sort_key is not a drop-in replacement here because overlint passes
bare version strings (e.g. "1.0.0") to sorted_versions(), not full cpvs,
so cpv_sort_key's catpkgsplit-based comparator would fall back to plain
string comparison. portage.util.cmp_sort_key(portage.vercmp) preserves
the original behaviour.

--- a/overlint/cli.py
+++ b/overlint/cli.py
@@ -126,7 +126,7 @@ def detect_ebuild_changes(overlay_path, category_package, original_overlay_path


 def sorted_versions(versions):
-	return sorted(versions, key=portage.versions.cmp_sort_key(portage.vercmp))
+	return sorted(versions, key=portage.util.cmp_sort_key(portage.vercmp))


 def dump_tree(tree, title):
